This place has awesome food, lots of tap beers, great cocktails, great service, and well organized with the reservation seating during covid. My vegetarian gf had "the best impossible burger" in her entire life. The televisions are well placed and perfect for game days. A Must try!

Ordered takeout from Brownstone last night and was really impressed; great variety of choices; wraps, salads, burgers, cheese curds, pretzels, soups. Normally I associate wraps with a kind of simple food option but was really impressed at the flavorful and tasty profile of the buffalo chicken wrap, cheese curds came with marinara and chipotle ranch and my gf's steak salad was cooked to a perfect medium rare.

The Brownstone is a great spot!! They have good food and good drinks! I have been to birthdays, baby showers, graduation parties, and Sunday football drinking here before. Always a good time! My latest trip here was when indoor dining was closed. It was cold outside but the waiter was nice to get the heat lamps going for us so it made it manageable! The food and drinks hit the spot! All there food is really good.

Ordered Saturday through Uber Eats -  delivery didn't show up due to Uber Eats issue. When I called, Adam @ Brownstone was SUPER helpful and they cooked a new order ASAP and another manager drove it over personally to make sure it got there quickly and was still warm. It even got a follow up call the next day to make sure we were satisfied with the meal. We really liked the food too, but the great service was really above and beyond! We will definitely go again & hopefully uber eats will get their act together :)

I was drawn to this restaurant because of its charming outdoor seating, nice location on Lincoln Ave, and seemingly foolproof bar-food menu. I could not have been more disappointed and disheartened after my visit. My boyfriend was served a steak sandwich with a noticeably sour tasing cheese, cold and tasteless onion rings, and my Mac and cheese was watery and bland. My boyfriend spent the entire rest of the night suffering from violent food poisoning. Do not be fooled by the charming exterior. This restaurant needs to take a serious reflective lens to their food safety and preparation.

Not so great for going to dinner with a group of friends that you might want to talk to though.  EDIT 4/26/17: Adam responded to this, but I don't think he actually read my comments. Despite alerting the waitstaff that we had a reservation, they told us it was a "Find a seat" situation, and we ended up squeezing around a somewhat small table.  I was not super displeased with my experience...but I'm a tad disappointed in Adam's response to my review.  Seems like he didn't even read any of it.

A serious decline overall over the past few months. We've been visiting Brownstone for over a year (as we live within 2 blocks), and recently they've made numerous changes to their regular & brunch menu items. The quality of the items has definitely suffered as a result. The chilaquiles for example lost avocado, cilantro, and radish -- yet the price stayed the same. It's an entirely different, much less expensive dish and now has much fewer ingredients...at the same price point.  Additionally, the service has severely suffered. We visited today for Brunch and were the only table occupied inside of the restaurant. There were only 2 tables occupied outside, for a total of 6-8 customers in the entire place during peak brunch hours on a Saturday. Our waitress seemed annoyed from the minute we declined drinks, and it showed through her poor attitude and horrendous service throughout our meal. By horrendous, I do mean she had to be reminded on 2 separate occasions by 2 co-workers that we needed our order taken, food removed, and our check...what a joke!  On our most recent visit, there were 4 workers in the place and we still waited 10+ minutes to have our order taken, went 10+ minutes without refills on water, the cook finally came to clear the 2 dirty plates (only at which point did our waitress realize we needed refills), and we had to track down the waitress (who was busy joking around with the other 3 workers) to receive our check AND again to pay it (we ultimately settled with a bartender). A meal that should have taken about 30-45 minutes took well over an hour, coupled with poor food and awful service.  Due to the sharp declines in both food quality and service, we've taken Brownstone off our brunch rotation and will instead focus on North Center's many premiere brunch spots...to name a few: Via Lima, ROCKS, Mrs. Murphy & Son's, and Danny Egghead's.
